.TH "vmw_resource_check_buffer" 9 "vmw_resource_check_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_resource_check_buffer \- Check whether a backup buffer is needed for a resource and in that case, allocate one, reserve and validate it.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_resource_check_buffer
.BI "(struct ww_acquire_ctx *ticket "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_resource *res "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ","
.BI "struct ttm_validate_buffer *val_buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ticket" 12
The ww aqcquire context to use, or NULL if trylocking.
.IP "res" 12
The resource for which to allocate a backup buffer.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Whether any sleeps during allocation should be
performed while interruptible.
.IP "val_buf" 12
On successful return contains data about the
reserved and validated backup buffer.
